  Multifactor Productivity                                     BLS-DOL  DOL Logo
  BLS Home  Programs & Surveys  Topics A-Z  Glossary  What's New


   Multifactor Productivity (MFP) measures the changes in output per unit
   of combined inputs. Indexes of MFP are produced for the private
   business, private nonfarm business, and manufacturing sectors of the
   economy. MFP is also developed for 2-and 3-digit Standard Industrial
   Classification (SIC) manufacturing industries, the railroad
   transportation industry, and the utility and gas industry.
